        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/07/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 17:07:09</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=5028"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5028')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4709&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=So+what+has+changed+Post+Balancing%3F"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I play a Level 52 Necromancer on The Rathe.  I could be level 54 by now, but I have stopped leveling to do quests (Chardok Faction) and replace out equipment (Camping and raising cash).  I'm a member of a Small Family guild which has an alliance with 2 other guilds.</P><P>Now that I fear that the main thrust of Caster balancing is over for the INT casters... what has changed? OH BTW I'm ignoring the NPC Caster changes...</P><P>Resist rates have been lowered on SOME raid level enounters.  Pets live a bit long thanks to life tap fix and Ripose fix.  Pets are somewhat more welcome on raids due to MEZ fix but are still bad with pathing.  Focus items make little change to our power.  Most our DD spell don't work with DD focus items and the Affliction line of Focus don't help us in most circumstances.</P><P>DOTs still don't stack.  They last longer which isn't that useful since most mobs die faster than existing unfocused DOTs.  Affliction Haste on DOTs really doesn't help and I can't remember last time I ran out of mana loading DOTs so Affliction efficancy is pointless as well.  This of course ignores the difficulty in obtaining level III versions of these items.</P><P>On the plus side.  Extended range, Casting haste, Mana preservation and Extend enchantment do work nicely with our support spells and DD spells.  The net effect on play is minimal.  You just don't cast enough of these spell in the right circumstance to notice a real improvment.</P><P>Dragon raids.  I can't land a spell on Naggy I suspect Vox is the same but never tried and since 52 is the level cap on this encounter all I can do is summon a pet and hope he does 500 damage in the time he is not running for his life.  I can also dump all my mana at a 3:1 ratio to a cleric or wizard who can do something with it.</P><P>Old world planes.  I can land spells, but most mobs last for less than 30 seconds therefore little point in cast DOTs.  I can use IR as a DD but not IB do to resulting screaming melee's.  I usualy cast EB as a DOT because it is fast enough to at least some damage then FD to get rid of agro.  I can also dump all my mana at a 3:1 ratio to a cleric or wizard who can do something with it.</P><P>Epic component raids.  Most times I can not land any spells on the mobs.  My pet is toasted by AOE or ran off by fear.  I usually try to cast a few times and then give my mana away since I can't make a difference.</P><P>Day to day grouping.  Very little has changed.  When I group people still compliment me on the array of things I can do to keep the group alive.  I still mez, heal, snare and DD.  I rarely ever DOT because the fights don't last long enough.  The focus items I have made me slightly more mana efficenet which didn't really help that much since I only ran out of mana whent he group is pushing really hard.   Oh, I can maintain MEZ on 3 mobs fairly reliably now, thanks to Casting haste.  People I group with are still amazed by my ability to hold agro with a single DOT on Gutterback.   I can reverse fear kite him until the melee's in the group can kill him.</P><P>Solo.  I fear - DOT almost all the time now that I don't have to worry about pet EXP.  It's sometimes a pain that I can't break mez on adds with my pet, but i can live with that.  I can imagine that the Affliction focus items make the biggest different here.  We can kill more mobs with less mana, but the unreliability of the extend affliction focus and the fact it doesn't seem to work with Splurt make necros continue to time dots like the were doing before the focus effects came.  They do this to avoid lost of damage output and darkness due to the flaky focus effects.  FD may or may not have improved.  I noticed situations where in Droga you could pull a mob, get a train, and FD, but as soon as you got up even after 15 mins everyone would be back to kill you.   I may have been unlucky, but 15 straight non failed FD and still getting trained makes me go HMM.  I died in that situation because /q with FD on didn't work as I remembered.  After the patch I haven't had this problem.</P><P>Another possible bug seems to be with Lich.  It seems to be hitting for alot more HP than it used to, but not consistantly.</P><P>I know this post is more or less a bitch fest, but I am trying to look at the possitive changes to the game.  I'm just having a lot of trouble seeing them right now.  As It stands right now i'm thinking my necro will be of no value to the guild once we start raiding more.  I'm begining to fear all I will be doing with Dartoth at level 60 is mining equipment for twink.</P><P><BR>Edited by - Dartoth Ickorkin on 06/07/2002  17:18:12</font></td>

      </tr>

